    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - DISASSEMBLY - REMOTE CONTROL (FIGURE 84)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="26">
        <title>REMOTE CONTROL (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302284">FIGURE 84</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302284" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302284" filename="../figg13/G1302284.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 84. Remote Control - Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four actuator shield assembly bolts and the shield (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302285">Figure 85</hotlnk>). Also remove the four actuator cover bolts and the cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302285" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302285" filename="../figg13/G1302285.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 85. Actuator Shield</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the air fitting nuts, making sure to keep the valve nuts from turning (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302286">Figure 86</hotlnk>). If you don't, you will accidentally disassemble the
                valves.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302286" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302286" filename="../figg13/G1302286.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 86. Loosen Air Fitting Nuts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The air fittings and lines can be removed as an assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302287">Figure 87</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302287" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302287" filename="../figg13/G1302287.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 87. Air Fittings &#38; Lines</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the valves. Note that they are marked "HI," "N" for neutral, and "LOW" (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302288">Figure 88</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302288" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302288" filename="../figg13/G1302288.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 88. Marked Valves</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the large and small O-ring from the bores of each valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302289">Figure 89</hotlnk>). Replace with new O-rings during reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302289" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302289" filename="../figg13/G1302289.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 89. O-Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the hitch pin and the override plunger (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302290">Figure 90</hotlnk>). Remove and replace the three O-rings on the plunger and
                plunger cap.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302290" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302290" filename="../figg13/G1302290.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 90. Hitch Pin &#38; Override Plunger</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove both housing end caps and gaskets (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302291">Figure 91</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302291" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302291" filename="../figg13/G1302291.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 91. Housing End Caps &#38; Gaskets</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pistons (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302292">Figure 92</hotlnk>). The easiest way to do this is to use a screwdriver and
                gently push the shift rack to remove each piston.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302292" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302292" filename="../figg13/G1302292.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 92. Remove Pistons</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace two O-rings on each inner piston and one O-ring on each outer piston (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302293">Figure 93</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302293" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302293" filename="../figg13/G1302293.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 93. O-Rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift rack from the actuator housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302294">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302294" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302294" filename="../figg13/G1302294.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 94. Shift Rack</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the tie rod assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302295">Figure 95</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302295" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302295" filename="../figg13/G1302295.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 95. Tie Rod Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolt, washer and selection lever (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302296">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302296" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302296" filename="../figg13/G1302296.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 96. Bolt, Washer &#38; Selection Lever</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolt and outer shift control lever (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302297">Figure 97</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302297" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302297" filename="../figg13/G1302297.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 97. Outer Shift Control Lever</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the tie down strap and remove the boot (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302298">Figure 98</hotlnk>). Replace the boot if it is cut or damaged.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302298" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302298" filename="../figg13/G1302298.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 98. Replace Boot</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the seal from the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302299">Figure 99</hotlnk>). Replace it with a new one during reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302299" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302299" filename="../figg13/G1302299.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 99. Remove Seal From Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the set screw and gently tap the shift rod through the shift finger and housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a0">Figure 100</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a0" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a0" filename="../figg13/G13022a0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 100. Set Screw &#38; Shift Rod</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts and the actuator cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a1" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a1" filename="../figg13/G13022a1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 101. Actuator Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the automatic switch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a2">Figure 102</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a2" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a2" filename="../figg13/G13022a2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 102. Automatic Switch</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the control arm, bolt and washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a3">Figure 103</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a3" filename="../figg13/G13022a3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 103. Control Arm, Bolt &#38; Washer</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Hold the shift shaft still as you remove the components. Holding the shaft will help prevent
                    damaging the control arm.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the housing plugs (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a4">Figure 104</hotlnk>). Replace the used O-rings with new ones prior to
                reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a4" filename="../figg13/G13022a4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 104. Housing Plugs</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift pistons from the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a5">Figure 105</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a5" filename="../figg13/G13022a5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 105. Shift Pistons</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not force both pistons out of the same side of the housing at the same time. Doing so might
                    bind the pistons.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place new O-rings on the pistons prior to reassembly. Remove and inspect the joiner pin.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shift shaft and shift fingers from the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a6">Figure 106</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a6" filename="../figg13/G13022a6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 106. Shift Shaft &#38; Fingers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace the shift shaft O-ring with a new one (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a7">Figure 107</hotlnk>). Carefully use a screwdriver to lift the ring over the
                keyway to prevent cutting the ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a7" filename="../figg13/G13022a7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 107. Replacing O-Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring to disassemble the shift fingers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a8">Figure 108</hotlnk>). Inspect the shaft and key for wear or damage. If either
                needs to be replaced, replace them as a set.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a8" filename="../figg13/G13022a8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 108. Disassembled Shift Fingers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Examine the housing for burrs, wear or damage (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13022a9">Figure 109</hotlnk>). Replace if necessary. Clean all reusable components
                prior to reassembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13022a9" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13022a9" filename="../figg13/G13022a9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 109. Examine Housing For Burrs</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
